    <p>
      In the following years, the proportion of coding to gaming shifted in favor of the first. I tried many languages and environments, including <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commodore_BASIC">BASIC</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AMOS_(programming_language)">AMOS</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turbo_Pascal">Turbo Pascal</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delphi_(software)">Delphi</a>, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%2B%2B">C++</a>. The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%2B%2BBuilder">C++ Builder's</a> VCL and editors were so much fun to work with back then. After all those experiments, I finally settled with C++.
    </p>

